{
  "texts": [
    "Various researchers have confirmed the significant effect of PIIT on selfefficacy (Chahal & Rani, 2022; Bubou & Job, 2022).",
    "As a result, it is suggested that:",
    "According to Bandura (1986), SE represents individuals' judgments in terms of \"their capabilities to organize and execute a course of action required to attain designated 1 3 types of performances\" (p. 391).",
    "It is seen as an individuals' belief in their own competence, and typically reflects the level of capability that an individual believes he/ she possesses (Christensen and Knezek, 2015).",
    "According to Bubou and Job (2022), self-efficacy is intricately connected to self-esteem and self-worth, denoting a person's level of confidence in a certain circumstance or event."
  ]
}